[DOC title="@guides/Markdown"]

	# Markdown showcase

	Every markdown feature a page supports, in one place. This `#` heading is
	the page title — the sidebar still says _Markdown_, from the entity
	`title`. Values interpolate from the script: gabi is at version {version}.

	## Emphasis and inline code

	Text can be **bold**, _italic_, _**both**_, ~~struck through~~, or
	`inline code`. A literal brace needs an escape: \{ like so \}.

	## Links

	- An [external link](https://svelte.dev) — opens in a new tab.
	- A [relative link](./colors) and an [anchor](#tables) stay in the app.
	- Autolinked: https://github.com/gabilungu/gabi

	## Images

	Served from the configured `static` folder at the site root:

	![A gradient banner reading "gabi static asset"](/sample.svg "Static assets work")

	## Lists

	1. Ordered lists
	2. Keep their numbers
	    1. And nest
	    2. With sub-items

	- Unordered lists
	- Use bullets
	    - And nest too

	### Task lists

	- [x] Ship components
	- [x] Publish to npm
	- [ ] Take over the world

	## Tables

	| Component | Sizes |                Notes |
	| :-------- | :---: | -------------------: |
	| Button    |   4   |  left-aligned column |
	| Input     |   4   |      centered column |
	| Textarea  |   4   | right-aligned column |

	## Blockquotes and alerts

	> An ordinary blockquote renders as a quiet aside.

	> [!NOTE]
	> Useful information that users should know, even when skimming.

	> [!TIP]
	> Helpful advice for doing things better or more easily.

	> [!IMPORTANT]
	> Key information users need to know to achieve their goal.

	> [!WARNING]
	> Urgent info that needs immediate user attention to avoid problems.

	> [!CAUTION]
	> Advises about risks or negative outcomes of certain actions.

	## Code

	Fences highlight and never execute — even sdoc or Svelte syntax:

	```svelte
	<script>
		let count = $state(0);
	</script>

	<Button text="Count: {count}" onclick={() => count++} />
	```

	```bash
	npm install gabi
	```

